# Mushajjir â€” CLI Agent Rules

## Project Overview
- Vue 3 + Vite + Pinia SPA
- Vue Flow canvas for node-based tree editing
- localStorage-based persistence (no backend)
- AI integration via OpenAI-compatible APIs (OpenRouter, DeepSeek, Grok)

## Conventions

### Code Style
- Use `eslint.config.js` (flat config) â€” ESLint v10 no longer supports `.eslintrc.*`
- Run `npm run lint` before committing; 0 errors required
- Run `npm run format` (Prettier) before committing
- Run `npm test` (vitest) before committing; all tests must pass
- Run `node benchmark/benchmark.mjs` to measure computed property performance
- Semi: false, singleQuote: true, trailingComma: all, printWidth: 120
- Self-closing void elements (`<input/>`) are used consistently â€” `vue/html-self-closing` is disabled
- Intentional `v-html` usage (markdown rendering) must be preceded by `<!-- eslint-disable-next-line vue/no-v-html -->`

### Git Workflow
- Local repo uses git worktrees â€” check `git remote -v` and `git log --oneline -3` before assuming state
- Always `git fetch origin` first and check `git log --oneline origin/main..HEAD` for divergence
- If local is behind: `git stash` â†’ `git pull --rebase origin main` â†’ `git stash pop`
- Never use `git format-patch` + `git am` across diverged branches â€” conflicts are guaranteed
- After merging/rebase, re-run `npm run lint -- --fix` and `npm run format`

### Editor Tooling
- The `editor` tool's `old_text â†’ new_text` replacement can corrupt indentation in `.vue` files
- Always run `npx prettier --write <file>` after using the editor tool on `.vue` files
- Prefer `run_commands` with `sed` or `cat` for precise line-level changes in complex files

### Dependencies
- Check versions before creating config files (e.g., ESLint v9+ uses flat config)
- Use `npm install --save-dev` for dev dependencies
- Semver ranges in package.json: use `^` for libraries, `latest` for apps (as is current convention)

### Issues
- Close issues with `gh issue close <number>` after pushing
- Use `gh issue view <number>` to read issue details

## Data Model

### Node Shape
Every node in the tree conforms to this shape (normalized by `normalizeNodeData()` in `treeUtils.js`):
```js
{
  id: string,                  // "node_<uuid>" or "root"
  type: 'task',                // always 'task'
  position: { x: number, y: number },
  data: {
    title: string,             // default 'Untitled task'
    content: string,           // default ''
    notes: string,             // default ''
    notesOpen: boolean,
    tags: string[],            // cleaned, max 28 chars
    parentId: string | null,
    childCount: number | null, // clamped 1..12
    taskStatus: 'todo' | 'in-progress' | 'blocked' | 'done',
    systemMessage: string,     // AI status/error
    collapsed: boolean,
    width: number,             // clamped 280..560, default 320
    height: number | null,     // clamped 230..760
  }
}
```
Computed (non-persisted) fields added to `flowNodes`: `progress`, `actualChildCount`, `hiddenDescendantCount`, `searchMatch`, `dimmed`, `relationDraftSourceId`.

### Edge Kinds
Two edge kinds, distinguished by `edge.data.kind`:
- **`hierarchy`**: Parent-child tree edges. Solid line (2px). Created via `createHierarchyEdge()`. Drives `childrenByParent`/`parentByChild` maps.
- **`relation`**: Cross-tree references. Dashed line (1.8px). Created via `createRelationEdge()`. Has optional `label`.

### Store Computed Pipeline (`treeStore.js`)
Key computed properties and their dependencies (simplified):
```
nodes + edges â†’ nodeById, childrenByParent, parentByChild
nodes + searchQuery â†’ matchingNodeIds â†’ searchContextIds
nodes + activeTagFilters â†’ tagVisibleIds
nodes â†’ collapsedHiddenIds â†’ visibleNodeIds (via tagVisibleIds + collapsedHiddenIds)
nodes + childrenByParent + nodeById â†’ progressByNode (recursive: leaf=status, parent=average)
all above â†’ flowNodes (final display nodes for Vue Flow)
edges + visibleNodeIds + focusedBranchIds â†’ flowEdges (final display edges)
```

Refer to `doc/architecture-reference.md` for the full dependency graph and details.

### Settings Schema
Persisted to localStorage key `mushajjir-settings-v1`:
```js
{
  general: { appName, defaultChildCount, theme },
  save: { folderPath, format },
  ai: { selectedProviderId, providers: [{ id, name, baseUrl, model, apiKey }] },
  prompts: { selectedDividePromptId, dividePrompts: [{ id, name, content }] },
}
```
Default providers: OpenRouter, DeepSeek, Grok/xAI. See `settingsService.js` for defaults.

### AI Provider Interface
All providers use OpenAI-compatible chat completions API:
- `divideTask()` â†’ expects JSON array of `{ title, content }` objects
- `reformulateTask()` â†’ expects JSON object `{ "title": "", "content": "" }`
- Uses `extractJsonArray()` / regex fallback for parsing
- Error handling via `systemMessage` on node data + `alert()` fallback
